10/02/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- The Human Rights Association announced on Wednesday (February 9th) the discovery of another suspected mass grave in the Bitlis province district of Tatvan.
The grave is believed to contain the remains of 33 people, likely murdered members of the outlawed Kurdistan Workers' Party.
Proceedings are under way to begin excavation work at three other suspected mass graves in the area.
(Hurriyet, Firat, Bianet - 09/02/11)
